reviews.text:
This is a really nice restaurant.  The interior is beautiful!  They have a wide choice of food and it is comparable to nl. They also have a fully vegetarian menu with vegetable meat.  We have ordered a few snacks, the calamari was not really tasty unfortunately, but the fries were fine.  The dessert and the fresh juices were very good!

Dit is echt een leuk restaurant. Het interieur is prachtig! Ze hebben een ruime keus aan eten en het is vergelijkbaar met nl. Tevens hebben ze volledig vegetarische kaart met plantaardig vlees. Wij hebben een paar hapjes besteld, de calamares was niet echt lekker helaas, maar de frietjes waren prima. Het toetje en de verse sapjes waren erg goed!

result.name: Classified New World Tower

reviews.text: One of my regular place for salad, $60 for a large box, which is good value for money in Central. Wish they can change the options more often as I do get a bit bored from time to time. You can also add smoked salmon or ham for extra $15, but they only give you 2 or 3 pieces.
Good food and service...
The Panini was the worst I ever had the chorizo was cold and thick and in edible   The chairs are hard and the Internet is in possible to connect to

Has an appoinment near New World Tower but I'm an hour early, so I went for a quick lunch at Classified.  Didn't expect really nice food,  but didn't expect lousy food too! Worst burger I ever had!  The Classidied Burger is just slighly warm,  almost cold!  The bun is cold on the top, and soggy on tge bottom! The beef is almost cold,  bacon is tough as cardboard paper! Fries not crunchy at all!  Cappucino is just warmed! This is worst than McDonald! And I was surprised to see they are using plastic cutleries! Very disappointed!
Staff not so friendly and take long time to wait for the food.
